
As a mechanism for storing artifacts in git (eg, release tarballs or other artifacts),
create them in refs/releases.

The default refspec for clone is +refs/heads/*:refs/remotes/$remote/*, so anything
under refs/releases/ stays out of normal clones.  To create one:

Create:
	cd build && make DESTDIR=${DESTDIR?} install
	idx=$(mktemp); rm "$idx"
	GIT_INDEX_FILE="$idx" GIT_WORK_TREE=${DESTDIR?} git add .
	tree=$(GIT_INDEX_FILE="$idx" git write-tree)
	rm "$idx"

	# The temporary index avoids clobbering your real index, and GIT_WORK_TREE
	# tells git to read file content from the external directory.  GIT_DIR
	# still needs to resolve to your repo (for object storage), so run
	# this from inside the repo or set GIT_DIR explicitly.

	commit=$(git commit-tree "$tree" -m "${version?} release artifacts")
	git update-ref refs/releases/${version?} "$commit"


Then push it:
	git push $remote refs/releases/${version?}

List available releases:
	git ls-remote $remote 'refs/releases/*'
